CHANGELOG
---------

Version 0.2
2009-Apr-15: (rodriguj@atc.us.es)
Fixed a bug that overflowed a short int in LeeBloque.
Primitive parameter checking done.
Endian stuff fixed. Tested on a MacIntel using a PPC only binary, with Rossetta.
Original SDL support moved to SDL_Mixer support.
Added SDL basic support.
Source code compiles and runs ok with:
- GNU/Linux, gcc, OSS support
- GNU/Linux, gcc, SDL support
- GNU/Linux, gcc, SDL_Mixer support
- MS Windows, Visual Studio 2005, native Win32 audio support
- MS Windows, Open WATCOM, native Win32 audio support
- MS Windows, C-Free (IDE for MinGW32), SDL support
- Mac OS X 10.5, XCode, SDL support

Version 0.1-fix
2009-Apr-15: (rodriguj@atc.us.es)
Added Makefile.osx for OSX support (SDL).

2009-Apr-14: (rodriguj@atc.us.es)
Added Win32 audio handling not depends on SDL anymore
Added Win32 specific semantics for issuing a binary open

2009-Apr-13: (Dylan Smith : http://spectrum.alioth.net)
Added SDL options to aid portability.

Version 0.1
2009-Apr-13: (rodriguj@atc.us.es) 
WinAmp TAP input plugin ported to a standalone Linux 
console application. First version.

TODO: probably, a lot.
BUGS: Surely, a lot.
